# Hooks and Filters

## Using Hooks
- Use `add_action()` for actions, `add_filter()` for filters
- Specify appropriate priority (default 10) and accepted arguments
- Use descriptive callback names prefixed with plugin namespace
- Remove hooks when needed with `remove_action()` / `remove_filter()`

## Creating Custom Hooks
- Create extensibility with `do_action()` and `apply_filters()`
- Name hooks with plugin prefix: `my_plugin_before_save`
- Document all custom hooks for other developers
- Pass relevant data as parameters

## Best Practices
- Keep callback functions focused and small
- Check if hook/function exists before using
- Use proper hook timing (init, wp_loaded, admin_init, etc.)
